{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6c42e566-4f5d-468f-97f6-bc291a138d7b","content":"Yes, you will hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Target Framework Problems:**\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** and **`net5.0`** — MSTest v3 dropped support for these. You must upgrade them to **`net6.0`** or later.\n- **`net462`** — Still supported; no issue here.\n\n**Package Changes:**\nMSTest v3 consolidates `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` into a single **`MSTest`** package. You'd replace both references with one.\n\n**Behavioral Breaking Changes to watch for:**\n- Class/assembly cleanup lifecycle changes (cleanup now runs *before* `Dispose`).\n- `TestContext` property is no longer required on test classes.\n- Some assert APIs have updated signatures.\n\n**Recommended migration path:**\n1. Update `TargetFrameworks` to `net6.0;net462` (or `net8.0`).\n2. Replace both package references with `<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />`.\n3. Review tests for any reliance on cleanup ordering.\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7aba6c7a-5431-4e58-b943-d611847a945a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is multi-targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 has some important compatibility changes to be aware of. Let me provide an assessment.\n\nKey issues:\n1. **MSTest v3 drops support for older TFMs.** MSTest v3 (the `MSTest` meta-package or `MSTest.TestFramework` 3.x) requires at minimum .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2. Let me think more carefully:\n   - `net462` — .NET Framework 4.6.2 should still be supported in MSTest v3.\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` are both out of support and no longer compatible with MSTest v3.\n\n2. MSTest v3 consolidates into a single `MSTest` package rather than splitting `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`.\n\n3. There are behavioral breaking changes in MSTest v3, including modifications to class and assembly cleanup lifecycle and `TestContext` behavior.\n\nThe core issue is that users targeting `net5.0` or `netcoreapp3.1` will face compatibility problems—they'll need to upgrade to `net6.0` or later to use MSTest v3.","outputTokens":655,"requestId":"602D:342B39:272EFD6:29AA224:6A04945D"},"id":"abe3838b-d4d9-446e-9496-e6353173a498","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:10:39.211Z","parentId":"a2211539-dc02-47a4-b0ba-94378e6030e4"}
